 can
change the research level for an empire in the Research tab of the Edit Emp=
ire
screen.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>To adjust the researc=
h level
simply move the slider to the left (lower technology level) or right (higher
technology level). Each level corresponds to a project level in the tech tr=
ees
in the Research screen. Thus level 2 means that all research projects in the
first two columns of each tech tree will be researched.<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>When you are ready, c=
lick the
&#8216;Apply New Tech Level&#8217; button to set the selected research level
for this empire.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Alternatively you can=
 choose
to select individual researched techs for the empire. To do this click the
button &#8220;Select Techs individually&#8221;. This will open an editable
version of the Research screen, allowing you to left-click (mark as researc=
hed)
or right-click (mark as unresearched) individual techs in any of the 3 rese=
arch
tabs. Simply close the Edit Research screen to apply the changes.<o:p></o:p=
></span></p>

